<HEADLINE>
AGENT IRWIN DIES, REPRESENTED CARDS' WILSON 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By KENT SOMERS  
 c.1999 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Jeff Irwin, a prominent Valley sports agent, died Saturday
morning at his Scottsdale home of an apparent heart attack.
</P>
<P>
   Irwin, 41, is survived by his wife, Christine; son, Daniel John,
15; and daughter, McKenna Christine, 12.
</P>
<P>
   Irwin was the agent for several notable players, including
Cardinals defensive tackle Bernard Wilson and Chicago Bears
cornerback Tom Carter.
</P>
<P>
   In past years, he had represented several other Cardinals,
including fullback Larry Centers and safety Lorenzo Lynch.
</P>
<P>
   ``He always seemed to be upbeat and have an optimistic view of
the world,'' Wilson said Tuesday shortly before services for Irwin
were held at the Ascension Lutheran Church in Paradise Valley. ``He
always kept his word to me. He will be missed.''
</P>
<P>
   Irwin also represented Channel 10 sportscaster Kevin McCabe.
</P>
<P>
   ``With me, he didn't stand to make any money, but he still gave
me the utmost attention,'' said McCabe, who remembers that Irwin
visited him at Cardinals training camp in Flagstaff shortly after
McCabe agreed to a new deal.
</P>
<P>
   ``He was drinking a Diet Coke and eating some Red Vines and
said, `This is what I made off of you,' '' McCabe said.
</P>
<P>
   Irwin also owned The Firm, a fitness center in Scottsdale.
</P>
<P>
   ``He was always in great shape and in a good frame of mind,''
said Sondra Como, who had worked for Irwin at his agency for eight
years. ``He had a great charisma and presence about himself.''
</P>
<P>
   Irwin coached his son's basketball team, the Arizona Heat, and
the family has asked that contributions be made to Arizona Heat
Basketball, 204 E. Tremaine Drive, Chandler, AZ 85255. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
