<SLUG> BC-VIDEO-MINI04-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    ``Sick'' masochist has power
 &HT;    By Steve Murray
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QR;  ``Sick: The Life and Death of Bob Flanagan, Supermasochist''
(unrated) _ This late performance artist was best known for nailing
his genitals to a plank. And you'll see him do it here. That tells
you whether you can stomach this graphic documentary, the bizarre
but real love story about Flanagan and his dominatrix/lover Sheree
Rose. Stricken with cystic fibrosis, Flanagan chose self-mutilation
as an art form, and a way to master his own fate. Rigorously
nonjudgmental, ``Sick'' has the power to shake up some of your most
basic assumptions. It's impressive but also appalling. Please don't
say I didn't warn you. Grade: A
</P>
<P>
   _ Steve Murray writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
