to peel. She felt strange _ weak and tender _ and her eyes and
mouth felt irritated.
</P>
<P>
   I am a dermatologist, and from Bill's description I had a good
idea of what was wrong with Mary.
</P>
<P>
   I found Mary in her bed, staring at the flickering images on the
TV. When I introduced myself she smiled and said, ``Hey.''
</P>
<P>
   ``I'd like to take a look at your skin,'' I said, ``if that's
