<P>
   CLINTON-CONGRESS (Washington) _ In a battle of dueling
legislative agendas, President Clinton challenges Republicans to
set aside 15 percent of budget surpluses to rescue Medicare as he
and congressional Democrats announce a ``Families First'' plan for
the year. For the GOP, House Speaker J. Dennis Hastert and Majority
