lawsuits against companies that fail to correct their year 2000
computer problems, the Senate Commerce Committee narrowly approves
legislation that would limit their liability and impose a 90-day
cooling off period so they could solve the problems without going
to court. By JENNIFER CORBETT DOOREN.
