   JOURNAL-LEBANON _ BEIRUT _ What do you do when you just lost
your job and all you have left is a couple billion dollars? If
you're former Lebanese Prime Minister Rafic Hariri, you invite a
thousand friends over for dinner every night for two weeks. That's
how Hariri marked the Moslem holy month of Ramadan. After
explaining to a couple journalists why his term as prime minister
is being wrongly maligned by the new government, he invited them to
his ``Iftar'' feast. (Kaplow, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
