<P>
   Entertainment and culture stories from The N.Y. Times News
Service for Thursday, March 4:
</P>
<P>
   FRANCE-MODERN-ART (Paris) _ Arts Abroad: France sponsors shows
to promote its contemporary art. By Judith H. Dobrzynski.
</P>
<P>
   KAZAN-HUAC (Hollywood) _ In interviews in the 1970s, Elia Kazan
justified his testimony before the House Un-American Activities
Committee. By Bernard Weinraub.
</P>
<P>
   BOOK-TALK (Undated) _ The weekly book column. By Martin Arnold.
</P>
<P>
   TAXES-BOOK-REVIEW (Undated) _ ``The Greedy Hand: How Taxes Drive
Honest Americans Crazy and What To Do About It,'' by Amity Shlaes
(Random House). Reviewed by Christopher Lehmann-Haupt.
