<HEADLINE>
TRAVEL BARGAINS: FREIGHTER; PARIS; VIETNAM; CRUISES 
</HEADLINE>
   (For release Sunday, March 7)  
 (bl)  
 By JANET PIORKO   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   FREIGHTER FOR LESS
</P>
<P>
   Ivaran Lines is offering a discount of $1,000 for the second
person in a category C outside double cabin on the freighter
Americana this spring. The saving is good on three departures _
March 19, April 9 and April 30 _ on a 21-day itinerary, which
leaves from Houston and includes Veracruz, Mexico; Puerto Limon,
Costa Rica; Cartagena, Colombia; La Guaira, Venezuela, and San
Juan, among other ports. The fare in category C, the standard level
outside cabin, is $4,914 a person, double occupancy, before the
second-person discount. Air fare is extra.
</P>
<P>
   The freighter, which accommodates 88 passengers, has a pool, a
sauna and a lounge with a baby grand piano. Cabins have color TV,
VCR and minibar. Information and reservations: (800) 451-1639 or
(201) 798-5656.
</P>
<P>
   PARIS FARES PARED
</P>
<P>
   Corsair, an airline owned by the French company Nouvelles
Frontieres, plans flights between New York's Kennedy International
Airport and Paris this summer with fares of $398 to $498 round
trip, depending on departure dates. The flights are to operate
Friday, Saturday and Wednesday from June 23 to Sept. 18.
Reservations: (800) 366-6387, and (212) 779-0600.
</P>
<P>
   VIETNAM, ESCORTED
</P>
<P>
   A 15-day Vietnam Discovery tour is offered by Smartours starting
at $1,799 a person, double occupancy, including air fare from Los
Angeles (New York departures are $100 extra round trip). The price
also covers hotels, local ground and air transportation, guided
sightseeing and many meals.
</P>
<P>
   The itinerary includes Bangkok, a cruise on Halong Bay, Hanoi,
Hue, Hoi-An and Ho Chi Minh City. Departures are from April through
March 2000. The lowest price is for the April 17 departure. A
millennium departure Dec. 18 costs $2,199, and most other trips
$1,899. Reservations: (800) 337-7773.
</P>
<P>
   ANNIVERSARY CRUISE
</P>
<P>
   A 20 percent discount for newlyweds or couples celebrating their
25th, 40th, 50th or 60th anniversaries this year is offered by KD
River Cruises of Europe on most 1999 sailings on the Rhine and its
tributaries, on the Main-Danube Canal and the Danube, and on the
Elbe. The discounts are not available in April, when most cruises
are already discounted. The line may limit the number of cabins
available at the special rate, depending on how many bookings it
has for a given departure.
</P>
<P>
   With the discount, a five-night Rhine cruise on the Deutschland,
from Amsterdam to Basel, stopping at Cologne, Koblenz, Speyer and
Strasbourg, ranges from $796 to $1,056. Three- and four-night Rhine
cruises, discounted, are $416 to $692. Those seeking the discount
must present a marriage certificate, or in the case of newlyweds, a
wedding announcement or invitation.
</P>
<P>
   Reservations or information: (800) 346-6525 from the eastern
United States, (800) 858-8587 from the West.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
