<P>
   OINKERS OF 1999
</P>
<P>
   A selection of citations by Citizens Against Government Waste
for ``dogged perseverance in the mad pursuit of pork.''
</P>
<P>
   _ The Technopork Award. To the $75 million Teacher Training in
Technology Program _ when there are already 86 other teacher
training programs.
</P>
<P>
   _ The Kick in the Ash Award. To Sen. Ted Stevens, R-Alaska,, for
a $2 million monitor to warn airplanes of volcanic ash.
</P>
<P>
   _ The Chicken You-Know-What Award. To Sen. Barbara Mikulski,
D-Md., for a $225,000 demonstration project to determine whether
poultry litter can generate electricity.
</P>
<P>
   _ The Congressional Narcissist Award. To Rep. Louis Stokes,
D-Ohio, for a $20.8 million grant to the Louis Stokes Cleveland VA
Center.
</P>
<P>
   _ The Leaving With a Jet Plane _ or Two _ Award. To former House
Speaker Newt Gingrich, R-Ga., for the $112 million contract to
build KC130J planes in his district.
</P>
<P>
   Source: Citizens Against Government Waste.
</P>
