<P>
   RESEARCH-TRIANGLE _ Companies employing nearly 39,000 people
said it's unlikely they would have moved to central North Carolina
if it weren't for the Research Triangle Park. That endorsement of
the 40-year-old park is part of an economic impact study showing
the average salary for the park's employees is $54,145 (Burritt,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   AFC-EBITDA _ AFC Enterprises, the parent company of Churchs
Chicken, Popeyes Chicken &AMP; Biscuits, Seattle Coffee, Cinnabon
International, and Chesapeake Bagel Bakery announced record
operating EBITDA of $87 million for 1998, an increase of $13.0
million or 17.6 percent. Operating EBITDA for the fourth quarter of
1998 was $31.6 million, which was up $7.2 million or 29.5 percent
(Atlanta journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   ALLIED-MEXICO _ ATLANTA _ Allied Holdings, the Decatur,
Ga.-based car-hauler, is setting up a new logistics business in
Mexico. Axis Logistica will be part of Allied's Axis Group
subsidiary. (Thurston, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   CHECKFREE _ ATLANTA _ Checkfree Holdings Corp. fell as much as
10 percent after Intuit Inc. said it is filing a complaint against
the maker of systems for paying bills via computer. Intuit, which
owns 19.9 percent of Checkfree, said Checkfree is not complying
with the terms of an agreement. (Clothier, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
