<P>
   CHIEFTAINS &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ The Chieftains are Ireland's most famous and
successful traditional group, and leader/founder Paddy Moloney has
always loved the way the band's sound blends with female vocalists.
That (and the music he heard as a youth at his grandmother's house)
was the inspiration for the new ``Tears of Stone'' CD, which pairs
the band with Joni Mitchell, Sinead O'Connor, Loreena McKennit,
Joan Osborne and many others. By DAVE FERMAN. Story has moved in
``e'' entertainment category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
