<TEXT>
<P>
   Here are the business news stories the Los Angeles Daily News
plans to move for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs
of Thursday, March 4, and thereafter. The stories will carry the
``f'' financial news category code unless otherwise noted. For
questions about stories, contact Stewart Slavin at at the Daily
News, (818) 713-3701.
</P>
<P>
   BANK-SNOOP (Los Angeles) _ The federal agencies that govern the
nation's banks and thrifts have quietly proposed regulations that,
if approved, would force financial institutions to keep track of
their customers' accounts for suspicious _ but perfectly legal _
activity. By Deborah Adamson. (Will also move in the ``a'' national
and ``n'' California news files.)
</P>
<P>
   DISNEY-HONG-KONG (Burbank, Calif.) _ Disney tries throwing a bit
of cold water on reports that it has agreed to build a theme park
in Hong Kong, insisting that it is only exploring such a deal. By
Dave McNary.
</P>
<P>
   CHATCOM-RESULTS (Los Angeles) _ ChatCom Inc. released grim
quarterly results Wednesday and warned that, unless it can
restructure its debt and/or find a company to merge with, it will
need to file for bankruptcy protection before the month is done. By
Ben Sullivan.
</P>
