<P>
   MONICA-HOMETOWN (Los Angeles) _ In her hometown of Brentwood,
presidential paramour Monica Lewinsky was the ``it girl'' on the
eve of her television interview and a day before her tell-all book
was set to be released. Along the streets of this tony enclave and
at Monica's alma mater, Beverly Hills High School, the talk was
Monica, Monica, Monica. By Steve Carney. (Will move in the ``a''
national and ``n'' California news files.)
</P>
<P>
   CHIMP-SURPRISE (Los Angeles) _ It is a zoo baby boom. Following
the surprise discovery of a pregnant chimp, handlers say two more
are with infants, even though the males were thought to be too
young to sire, had vasectomies or just plain uninterested in
breeding. So now four of the seven adult female chimpanzees at the
Los Angeles Zoo are taking birth control pills. By Michael Coit.
(Will move in the ``a'' national and ``n'' California news files.)
</P>
<P>
   LA-SCHOOL-NURSES (Los Angeles) _ Los Angeles school officials
