nation's banks and thrifts have quietly proposed regulations that,
if approved, would force financial institutions to keep track of
their customers' accounts for suspicious _ but perfectly legal _
activity. By Deborah Adamson. (Will move in the ``a'' national,
``n'' California and ``f'' financial news files.)
