require special care during the school day are entitled to that
care at public expense, the Supreme Court rules, as long as the
services can be provided by someone other than a doctor. The 7-2
decision upholds lower court rulings that required an Iowa school
district to provide a trained aide to monitor the needs of a
quadriplegic boy who was dependent on a ventilator. By Linda
Greenhouse.
</P>
<P>
   GERIATRIC-CARE (Newport Beach, Calif.) _ Geriatric care
managers: an occupation born in response to the nation's rapidly
aging population and the health care system's complexity. Part
counselors and part social workers, they help manage the health
care, living arrangements and other affairs of their elderly
clients. They perform a role once filled by families _ not only
because families have become so scattered and care has become more
complicated, but also because outsiders are listened to, while
children often are not. By Sara Rimer. With photo. 1,700 words.
(MOVED)
