<P>
   TRADE-BANANA (Washington) _ The United States escalates two
politically contentious trade disputes with Europe, slapping 100
percent tariffs on $520 million in European products and
threatening to ban Europe's supersonic pride, the Concorde, from
landing in the United States. By David E. Sanger. (We plan to move
the story by 8:30 p.m. ET in ``i'' news file.) 1,300 words.
