<P>
   WINDS-BRIDGE (SEATTLE) _ The 520 bridge, which sustained serious
mechanical damage after winds and waves pummeled it Wednesday
morning, may not open for another 24 hours, probably after Thursday
morning's commute. Damage was the worst since the Jan. 20, 1993,
Innaugural Day storm when waves whipped by winds of up to 80 mph
bashed the floating bridge, fraying anchor cables and causing
cracks in the concrete pontoons.
