<HEADLINE>
TEST YOUR LITERARY KNOWLEDGE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Here's the urban-version geography puzzler, not likely to be any
easier than the state-oriented quiz. The challenge is to match the
titles of some quite varied literary works with their proper
authors. You pass with nine correct answers (a simple majority) and
earn an A with 12 right.
</P>
<P>
   The titles:
</P>
<P>
   1. ``Boston Beguine'' (song)
</P>
<P>
   2. ``Chattanooga Choo-Choo'' (song)
</P>
<P>
