   NY-MAYOR-SCHOOLS (New York) _ Drawing an ideological line over
an emotionally charged issue in public education, Schools
Chancellor Rudy Crew has informed Mayor Rudolph Giuliani that he
will resign if the administration succeeds in lobbying the Board of
Education to establish an experimental voucher program in which tax
dollars would be spent on sending children to private schools. By
Dan Barry. (Scheduled to move by 9:15 p.m. ET in ``a'' news file.)
</P>
