   (NYT15) WASHINGTON -- March 03, 1999 -- GREENSPAN-SOCSEC, 3-03
-- Federal Reserve Chairman Alan Greenspan testifies before the
House Commerce Sub-committee about reforming the Social Security
system on Wednesday. If budget surpluses now are going to help pay
for Social Security in the future, the key issue confronting
Congress is how to make sure the extra money is somehow saved,
Greenspan said. (Justin Lane/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT14) WASHINGTON -- March 03, 1999 -- CLINTON-DEMS, 3-03 --
President Clinton is applauded during a rally at the Library of
