<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-UGANDA-KIDNAP-NYT (moved on Tuesday, Mar. 2)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Tuesday, Mar. 2,
about the killing of eight tourists in Uganda referred incorrectly
in some copies to the headquarters location of the two American
victims' employer, the Intel Corporation. While the two worked in
Oregon, the company headquarters is in Santa Clara, Calif.
</P>
</TEXT>
