</P>
<P>
   JERUSALEM _ The police interrogated Foreign Minister Ariel
Sharon on the suspicion that he might have bribed a former general
to give false testimony on his behalf in a libel case. Sharon's
lawyer, Yaakov Weinroth, strongly denies that there was either any
act of bribery or any false testimony. &QL;
