   CHINA: Call for Tiananmen Inquiry
</P>
<P>
   BEIJING _ As the 10th anniversary of the June 4 killings by the
military around Tiananmen Square approaches, victims and their
families have renewed calls for the government to re-evaluate the
incident. The group wants to clarify who ordered soldiers to move
against the demonstrators, and a new compensation law for the
victims, whom they number in the tens of thousands.
