</P>
<P>
   Health Minister Nkosazana Zuma reaffirmed that the government
would not pay for AZT for pregnant women to prevent transmission of
the AIDS virus to their babies. Some foreign researchers are so
incensed at the decision that they are trying to embarrass her by
revoking her invitation to next year's World AIDS Conference, to be
held in South Africa.
</P>
