<SLUG> BC-BKN-LAKERS-NOTES-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
JONES TRADE NEAR?
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By HOWARD BECK  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   INGLEWOOD _ If the rumors are true, Eddie Jones has but four
games left in a Lakers uniform. And the ``if'' part of this
continuing saga of speculation will soon give way to facts, one way
or the other.
</P>
<P>
   The NBA's trade deadline is seven days away. But the
long-rumored swap of Jones and Elden Campbell for Charlotte's Glen
Rice, J.R. Reid and B.J. Armstrong could happen before 3 p.m. on
March 11 arrives.
</P>
<P>
   The Winston-Salem Journal reported this week that the trade will
be consummated once Rice is activated from the injured list,
possibly within days, and quoted one of the Hornets involved in the
deal as saying, ``I'm more positive that it is going to happen than
I have ever been.''
</P>
<P>
   Additionally, Portland coach Mike Dunleavy told reporters the
Trail Blazers wanted to trade for Rice but that their offer of
Isaiah Rider and Jermaine O'Neal couldn't beat the Lakers' offer.
</P>
<P>
   Lakers executive Jerry West is tired of the speculation.
</P>
<P>
   ``Until we do something, I refuse to talk about it or not talk
about it,'' he said. ``To me it's one of the things that's most
annoying; everyone speculating something certainly doesn't
necessarily mean it's going to happen. There may not be any
interest in doing anything here. . . .
</P>
<P>
   ``I look at Eddie Jones right now. I feel terrible for him. I
do,'' West said.
</P>
<P>
   But West wouldn't dismiss or confirm the rumor, leaving minds to
wander.
</P>
<P>
   ``But I've told you before, if we think we can improve our team,
we'll try to improve our team,'' West said. ``But to say something
is imminent, that's absolutely 100 miles from home base.''
</P>
<P>
   New title, same guy: Kurt Rambis' ascension to head coach hasn't
changed his pregame routine. Despite the added responsibilities,
he's out on the court each night, working out the rookies and bench
players and working up a sweat.
</P>
<P>
   Afterward, he meets with the media in T-shirt and shorts, and
sometimes no shoes.
</P>
<P>
   ``That's Kurt, he's still gonna go out before the game and work
out with the rookies, still have on a wrinkly T-shirt and wrinkly
shorts,'' Derek Fisher said. ``Most head coaches, they've already
got their suit on at 10 o'clock in the morning. We're probably
going to have to do a pool and see if we can get Kurt some threads.
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't think he'll change at all. I think he can do this for
20 years and still be the same guy.''
</P>
<P>
   Bailey's back: Former UCLA guard and Lakers draft pick Toby
Bailey was in uniform for the Phoenix Suns on Wednesday, having
been activated off the injured list. Bailey, drafted in the second
round last June and promptly traded to the Suns, appeared in five
games earlier this season before going on the injured list with a
knee problem.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
